Original TODO items:

* Add real optimization for odd-length FFTs, possibly using DST.
* Add real optimization to the n-dimensional FFT.
* Add a simple windowing function, such as Hamming:
  `w(i) = .54 - .46 * cos(2 * pi * i / (n - 1))`.
* Make fixed-point scaling and bit shifts easier to configure.
* Document or revisit input/output FFT scaling.
* See whether fixed-point code can be optimized further without adding
  complexity.
* Document the overlap-tail-scrap fast convolution filtering in
  `kiss_fastfir.c`.
* Test all `tools/` code with fixed point. The original README noted that
  `kiss_fastfir.c` did not work at the time, and possibly other tools had
  similar issues.


